msgctxt "an5.139:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ekena vā saravegena viddho, dvīhi vā "
"tīhi vā catūhi vā pañcahi vā saravegehi viddho saṃsīdati visīdati, na "
"santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders when "
"struck by a swift arrow, or by two, three, four, or five swift arrows. It "
"doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle."

msgctxt "an5.139:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ. (5)"
msgstr "That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure touches."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.139:7.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo na rājāraho hoti "
"na rājabhoggo na rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"A royal bull elephant with these five factors is not worthy of a king, not "
"fit to serve a king, and is not considered a factor of kingship."

# See BB’s note on dhamma vs. anga here. Note also that the Thai edition has dhamma.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.139:8.1"
msgid ""
